data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

**EF Core 11 fully removes sync I/O for the Cosmos DB provider.** In .NET 10 you had `EnableSyncIo()` as an opt-in — that opt-in no longer exists. All synchronous calls (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`, etc.) now **always throw** at runtime. There is no workaround.

### Fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- Every sync LINQ operator → its `*Async` counterpart
- Methods return `Task<T>` / `Task` and callers must `await`
- This will ripple up the call chain — controllers/services calling these methods must also become async
- Remove any `EnableSyncIo()` configuration since it's no longer recognized
